article.headline: Mississippi St. 102, North Alabama 61
article.story: STARKVILLE, Miss. -- Barry Stewart and Jarvis Varnado scored 16 points each to lead Mississippi State to a 102-61 victory over North Alabama on Wednesday night. Varnado also added 14 rebounds for the Bulldogs (3-0), who hit a season-high 11 3-pointers in the game en route to their third win in five days. North Alabama (2-1) managed to hit only 23 of 72 shots in the game, and was stymied by the Bulldog defense for most of the second half. Stewart was 5 of 8 from the field, including 3 of 5 from behind the arc. Varnado, last season's Southeastern Conference blocks leader, had seven blocks in the game. It was Varnado's eighth career double-double. Romero Osby added 15 points on 5-of-9 shooting, and Elgin Bailey chipped in 10.
